WEBVTT

00:20.103 --> 00:22.522
I cannot believe
there are no charging stations.

00:23.523 --> 00:25.025
Fucking Arizona.

00:26.901 --> 00:29.070
Well, we could call a tow,

00:29.154 --> 00:32.198
but, uh, you know, what the fuck,
it's gonna take way too long.

00:32.657 --> 00:33.867
Let's just take the PJ.

00:34.284 --> 00:35.994
I know jets are wasteful,

00:36.077 --> 00:38.079
but I don't want you driving
through the night,

00:38.163 --> 00:39.247
and my mom...

00:39.748 --> 00:41.458
really hates it when people are late.

00:42.167 --> 00:44.127
God, I cannot wait for you to meet her.

00:46.713 --> 00:48.506
-What time is Love getting there?
-Who knows?

00:48.590 --> 00:50.884
She's on her new boyfriend's dick
like herpes.

00:50.967 --> 00:52.552
Don't get me wrong, I love the guy, but--

00:52.635 --> 00:54.804
Will, right? She's bringing him?

00:55.180 --> 00:56.014
Yep.

00:59.100 --> 01:00.185
<i> Move, Joe.</i>

01:00.643 --> 01:01.936
Wait, stop! Stop!

01:02.228 --> 01:03.313
Stop, Candace.

01:03.396 --> 01:04.314
I love you.

01:04.397 --> 01:05.523
Just let me go.

01:05.607 --> 01:06.983
Tell me you don't love me.

01:07.067 --> 01:09.736
I don't! I don't love you.

01:10.070 --> 01:11.321
I never have.

01:12.363 --> 01:14.199
What are you gonna do about it, Joe?

01:15.075 --> 01:16.117
Don't do this!

01:16.785 --> 01:17.660
Stop!

01:26.419 --> 01:29.839
Looks like it's gonna be
a proper meet-the-parents Wellkend.

01:30.590 --> 01:31.549
Oh!

01:31.633 --> 01:32.592
Hi. Yeah.

01:32.675 --> 01:34.010
Forty Quinn here.

01:34.094 --> 01:36.304
Yes, like the number, but spelled out.

01:36.387 --> 01:38.098
F-O...

01:49.359 --> 01:52.737
<i> I now truly understand</i>
<i>the term "love of my life."</i>

01:53.613 --> 01:55.865
<i>My life makes sense now with you in it.</i>

01:56.241 --> 01:58.827
<i>Complete. Not closed.</i>

01:59.285 --> 02:02.789
<i>More open to the world</i>
<i>and everything beautiful than ever before.</i>

02:03.623 --> 02:04.958
<i>Nothing to hide.</i>

02:05.333 --> 02:07.210
<i>You've asked me to meet the parents.</i>

02:07.293 --> 02:08.920
<i>Might be messy, family can be.</i>

02:09.003 --> 02:11.714
<i>But whatever comes,</i>
<i>we'll get through it, together.</i>

02:14.801 --> 02:16.136
I don't wanna.

02:16.386 --> 02:18.263
Can your parents really be that bad?

02:18.930 --> 02:20.932
Worse. They can be worse.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.101
Okay, remember,

02:23.184 --> 02:25.770
they charm so that they can manipulate.

02:26.146 --> 02:27.897
My mom is a lot.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.649
Just give in to her crazy.

02:29.732 --> 02:31.693
And my dad is impenetrable.

02:31.985 --> 02:33.528
Just don't take it personally.

02:34.154 --> 02:35.071
Try not to.

02:35.155 --> 02:36.239
I still do.

02:36.322 --> 02:38.491
Is there anything I can do to support you?

02:39.409 --> 02:40.410
We could have a signal.

02:40.910 --> 02:41.828
Like...

02:42.787 --> 02:45.248
What is that? Are... Are you Spider-Man?

02:45.331 --> 02:47.667
No, no.

02:47.750 --> 02:49.460
Um, it's-- it's, uh...

02:50.128 --> 02:51.713
ASL for "I love you."

02:52.255 --> 02:55.884
In, like, a friendly
you know, like, platonic way.

02:57.093 --> 02:58.011
<i> I love you.</i>

02:58.803 --> 03:00.555
<i>In the non-friendly way,</i>

03:01.097 --> 03:03.099
<i>but I'm waiting to say it.</i>

03:03.183 --> 03:04.934
<i>Why rush when we have</i>
<i>the rest of our lives?</i>

03:05.894 --> 03:07.020
Hmm!

03:08.354 --> 03:09.606
My dad's gonna like that shirt.

03:09.856 --> 03:11.566
<i> I know. I do my research.</i>

03:12.275 --> 03:15.820
<i>America's surrogate dream parents,</i>
<i>Ray and Dottie Quinn.</i>

03:16.196 --> 03:17.864
<i>Ray is a Pasadena golden boy</i>

03:17.947 --> 03:19.449
<i>who comes from old-school money.</i>

03:19.532 --> 03:22.327
<i>Dottie is the spark plug</i>
<i>that gives him life.</i>

03:22.410 --> 03:24.370
<i>They met in the naked hot tubs</i>
<i>at Esalen, </i>

03:24.454 --> 03:25.705
<i>eloped shortly thereafter.</i>

03:25.788 --> 03:28.166
<i>Joan Baez is rumored to have officiated.</i>

03:28.917 --> 03:32.295
<i>Dottie opened Anavrin</i>
<i>with Ray's family cash.</i>

03:32.378 --> 03:34.505
<i>What started as a pet project has evolved</i>

03:34.589 --> 03:37.175
<i>into a global brand largely due to Dottie,</i>

03:37.842 --> 03:40.720
<i>all centered on the Quinn family motto,</i>

03:40.803 --> 03:42.889
<i>"Transparency and realness."</i>

03:43.723 --> 03:45.642
<i>This weekend is Ray and Dottie's</i>
<i>30th anniversary,</i>

03:45.725 --> 03:47.518
<i>and they're making up</i>
<i>for their quickie wedding</i>

03:47.602 --> 03:49.145
<i>with a wellness bacchanal.</i>

03:49.229 --> 03:51.231
<i>Ray and Dottie's vow renewal</i>
<i>will be the culmination</i>

03:51.314 --> 03:53.107
<i>of packed community--</i>
<i>say it with me now--</i>

03:53.358 --> 03:54.359
<i>"Wellkend."</i>

03:54.442 --> 03:56.444
<i>Shoot me in the face.</i>

03:56.527 --> 03:58.029
<i>But whatever you need, Love.</i>

03:58.112 --> 04:01.866
<i>These people may pretend to be real,</i>
<i>but you and I really are.</i>

04:04.118 --> 04:06.204
-<i> Speaking of messy family...</i>
-Hey.

04:06.287 --> 04:09.457
<i>Did you know Ja Rule</i>
<i>and Ashanti never banged?</i>

04:09.540 --> 04:10.625
Okay. And?

04:10.708 --> 04:13.920
I don't know, it just kind of ruins it
for me knowing their love was never real.

04:14.003 --> 04:16.422
Can you check out?
It fucks up inventory when you steal.

04:17.340 --> 04:20.426
-Is that kombucha?
<i>-Stop being so codependent, okay?</i>

04:20.510 --> 04:24.430
'Buch has about as much alcohol in it
as fresh-pressed juice,

04:24.514 --> 04:26.599
and I want to pour one out for Henderson.

04:27.725 --> 04:28.851
Because it was our thing.

04:29.435 --> 04:31.854
<i> Did you hear they're saying</i>
<i>it was a suicide now?</i>

04:32.939 --> 04:34.440
<i>Too good for this world.</i>

04:35.358 --> 04:38.152
<i> Another melancholy clown</i>
<i>dies by his own hand,</i>

04:38.236 --> 04:40.613
<i>and his adoring fans</i>
<i>and acquaintances grieve deeply</i>

04:40.697 --> 04:43.074
<i>for, oh, about the next one</i>
<i>to two news cycles.</i>

04:43.866 --> 04:45.368
Are you making it to meetings?

04:45.451 --> 04:47.203
I'm in such a positive place right now

04:47.287 --> 04:49.998
and AA is a breeding ground of negativity.

04:50.540 --> 04:51.708
Speaking of circle jerks,

04:51.791 --> 04:53.710
<i>you still coming to Mom and Dad's</i>
<i>Wank-end?</i>

04:53.793 --> 04:55.128
Yes, of course.

04:56.504 --> 04:58.506
Forty, just promise me
that you won't do anything--

04:58.589 --> 04:59.966
Gotta go. Amy's in the whip.

05:04.762 --> 05:05.930
Is everything okay?

05:06.014 --> 05:06.931
Yeah.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.686
No.

05:12.103 --> 05:14.605
Forty's gonna go off the rails again.
I can tell.

05:15.231 --> 05:16.399
It's gonna be bad.

05:16.482 --> 05:18.359
You like the girl he just met, right?

05:20.403 --> 05:21.321
Sure.

05:22.196 --> 05:23.364
We went to the movies.

05:24.198 --> 05:25.283
We didn't even talk.

05:26.284 --> 05:28.286
What can I say? He's on pattern.

05:28.369 --> 05:32.123
Meets a girl, each a new
impossible-to-predict type of bad for him,

05:32.206 --> 05:34.625
and then he tries
to get our parents to like her,

05:34.709 --> 05:36.878
then he flings himself off a cliff
when they don't.

05:36.961 --> 05:38.713
<i> Leaving you to clean the splatter.</i>

05:38.921 --> 05:40.256
I can neutralize.

05:40.840 --> 05:42.884
I can distract. I'm good with parents.

05:44.761 --> 05:45.636
We got this.

05:46.179 --> 05:48.765
Sure, I could tell you
were my sister is, but...

05:48.848 --> 05:49.891
what is this about?

05:50.350 --> 05:51.684
It's about Joshua Bunter.

05:51.768 --> 05:53.394
-You might know him as...
- <i>Henderson.</i>

05:53.478 --> 05:55.646
<i>Clearly, I need to be</i>
<i>in two places at once,</i>

05:55.730 --> 05:57.106
<i>with you and near Ellie.</i>

05:57.190 --> 05:58.274
Just crossing the T's here.

05:58.358 --> 06:01.361
We know from Henderson's IMs he was
planning on seeing your sister that night.

06:02.153 --> 06:04.238
Yeah, I don't read the news.

06:04.322 --> 06:06.699
It's, like, so depressing,
but I-- I thought he...

06:07.825 --> 06:08.701
offed himself.

06:08.868 --> 06:10.411
<i> Delilah's smarter than these guys.</i>

06:10.495 --> 06:12.330
Yeah, well, it seems that way.

06:12.413 --> 06:15.750
<i> And I've got parental tech</i>
<i>to keep an eye on Ellie</i>

06:15.833 --> 06:18.836
<i>and the fallout</i>
<i>from Hendy's tragic suicide.</i>

06:18.920 --> 06:20.296
Well, Ellie's not home right now,

06:20.380 --> 06:23.549
but I can call you when she is
if you want, or, like...

06:23.633 --> 06:26.177
Oh, no. I have to go into work.

06:26.469 --> 06:27.387
I'm sorry.

06:27.845 --> 06:28.679
Bye.

06:36.687 --> 06:38.606
Were you at Henderson's
the night he died, Ellie?

06:39.649 --> 06:40.525
What are these?

06:43.653 --> 06:45.863
-What do you think they are?
-Don't evade with a question.

06:45.947 --> 06:47.865
-You evaded with a question first!
-Jesus!

06:47.949 --> 06:49.617
Half the time you treat me like an adult,

06:49.700 --> 06:52.870
but, wait, suddenly, I'm a kid because
you can't get it together to be an adult?

06:52.954 --> 06:54.122
You really wanna know?

06:56.833 --> 06:58.251
Those are Henderson's.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.671
No, they're not.

07:02.672 --> 07:03.840
They're random.

07:03.923 --> 07:05.967
They're... He's not even in 'em.
They're just...

07:06.050 --> 07:07.051
I know...

07:09.762 --> 07:11.139
because he did it to me.

07:15.476 --> 07:16.394
I don't believe you.

07:18.563 --> 07:21.482
-Where's your photo then?
-You don't believe me? You need proof?

07:22.984 --> 07:26.612
Listen, don't get mad at me because
he was a bad guy and you fell for it.

07:26.696 --> 07:27.989
He was my friend!

07:28.072 --> 07:30.116
He wasn't your friend, Ellie!
Let me guess.

07:30.199 --> 07:33.077
He made you promise not to tell anyone
you were hanging out alone together?

07:33.161 --> 07:34.162
Basic predator move.

07:34.245 --> 07:36.247
You are a lot of things...

07:36.747 --> 07:38.207
but you're not stupid.

08:04.817 --> 08:07.195
Ah, ooh, ooh! Hi.

08:07.278 --> 08:08.946
-Hello.
-Hi, babe.

08:09.030 --> 08:11.073
Oh, my God,
I'm so glad you guys are here.

08:11.157 --> 08:12.158
Oh, my God.

08:13.242 --> 08:14.702
-How are you?
-I'm good.

08:14.785 --> 08:15.953
Yeah, this is great.

08:16.037 --> 08:18.289
<i> Well, thankfully,</i>
<i>teenagers text emotional gibberish,</i>

08:18.372 --> 08:19.832
<i>so I know Ellie's okay.</i>

08:19.916 --> 08:21.584
All right, put the phone away.

08:22.793 --> 08:24.378
Welcome to the Hellmouth.

08:25.838 --> 08:27.715
<i> And I'm in a Wes Anderson movie</i>

08:27.798 --> 08:30.051
<i>set in a weirdly Caucasian ashram.</i>

08:30.676 --> 08:31.969
-Hey, Dad.
-Lovey, hey.

08:32.053 --> 08:33.012
Hey.

08:33.095 --> 08:34.347
This is Will Bettelheim.

08:34.597 --> 08:36.140
Oh. You related to Bruno?

08:36.224 --> 08:38.142
<i> Ray's a not-so-secret fantasy fan.</i>

08:38.226 --> 08:40.061
<i>He's referring to Bruno Bettelheim,</i>
<i>author of...</i>

08:40.144 --> 08:42.063
<i>The Uses of Enchantment </i>is a classic.

08:42.355 --> 08:45.107
No relation, I'm just a fan.
It's good to meet you, Mr. Quinn.

08:45.816 --> 08:46.817
Call me Ray.

08:47.109 --> 08:47.944
Will?

08:48.945 --> 08:50.655
Finally we meet.

08:51.239 --> 08:52.156
Oh!

08:52.448 --> 08:53.908
You are delicious.

08:53.991 --> 08:55.409
The pleasure is all mine, Dottie.

08:55.493 --> 08:57.203
Come here, darling. You look beautiful.

08:57.286 --> 08:59.288
-Hey, Mom.
-I'm sorry, I'm all over the place.

08:59.372 --> 09:01.249
-Let's get you a drink.
-Okay.

09:03.084 --> 09:04.293
Sounds good.

09:07.922 --> 09:10.007
-Forty.
-Sport! Hi, Love.

09:10.091 --> 09:11.801
Where'd she go? There she is.

09:12.301 --> 09:13.427
You gotta meet my girl, Amy.

09:13.511 --> 09:14.804
Amy, come here.

09:22.311 --> 09:23.729
Hi there.

09:25.147 --> 09:26.274
Will Bettelheim,

09:26.357 --> 09:27.275
Amy Adam.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.110
Nice to meet you.

09:29.193 --> 09:30.236
<i> It can't be.</i>

09:30.319 --> 09:31.946
<i>Am I hallucinating?</i>

09:32.488 --> 09:34.407
<i>This is her hand, this is real.</i>

09:34.490 --> 09:35.491
<i>Candace is here.</i>

09:35.575 --> 09:36.492
Will Bettelheim...

09:36.576 --> 09:38.035
What a great name.

09:38.536 --> 09:39.704
Almost sounds made up.

09:40.204 --> 09:42.290
<i> Is she trying to spar with me?</i>

09:42.373 --> 09:44.458
That's funny, I was just thinking,
"Amy Adam."

09:44.542 --> 09:46.460
How totally un-google-able.

09:48.254 --> 09:50.965
<i> This is a game to her.</i>
<i>She's enjoying this.</i>

09:51.048 --> 09:52.425
I'm so happy to see you again.

09:52.800 --> 09:54.552
<i> She's crazy, Love.</i>

09:54.802 --> 09:56.846
I'm also so hungry
I could eat my own hand, so let's--

09:56.929 --> 09:59.557
-Oh, no, don't worry. Just eat mine.
-Oh!

09:59.682 --> 10:02.143
<i> Like the kids say, "Fuck my life."</i>

10:15.531 --> 10:16.991
Oh, good, you're awake.

10:17.617 --> 10:19.327
-Shh-sh-sh-sh.

10:19.535 --> 10:21.454
It's okay, you are totally safe.

10:22.580 --> 10:23.914
I have a surprise for you.

10:29.712 --> 10:31.255
Can you promise to be calm?

10:32.798 --> 10:34.175
Okay, good.

10:36.510 --> 10:39.013
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean what I said. I'm an idiot.

10:39.096 --> 10:40.681
Okay, I'm stupid. Let's just go home.

10:40.765 --> 10:43.225
You're just saying that
because you think it's what I wanna hear.

10:43.309 --> 10:44.977
No, I'm saying that

10:45.061 --> 10:47.605
because I'm tied up in the back of a van.

10:47.688 --> 10:48.856
I had to...

10:49.273 --> 10:50.608
so we could get here...

10:51.025 --> 10:52.068
to talk.

10:52.151 --> 10:53.277
I am so sorry.

10:55.279 --> 10:57.907
-But it's all gonna be worth it.
-Where are we?

10:58.449 --> 10:59.408
Lake Mahopac.

11:00.284 --> 11:03.329
You remember that amazing picnic we had?
I brought all your faves again.

11:04.038 --> 11:05.414
No, just, okay...

11:05.498 --> 11:07.625
I know-- I know you don't want to hurt me.

11:07.708 --> 11:09.794
-I would never hurt you.
-Just untie me. Untie me.

11:09.877 --> 11:11.879
I can't do that yet, you know I can't.

11:12.630 --> 11:13.631
Just hang on.

11:23.182 --> 11:24.767
Thanks. Thank you.

11:29.105 --> 11:30.064
Candace!

11:40.866 --> 11:42.868
Listen, you don't understand.
Don't do this!

11:42.952 --> 11:45.371
Stop! Please, don't do this!
Shh! Sh-sh-sh-sh!

11:45.538 --> 11:46.372
Stop...

11:46.455 --> 11:47.373
-Stop!

12:04.515 --> 12:05.474
<i> How?</i>

12:05.558 --> 12:07.435
<i>How did she manage this?</i>

12:07.518 --> 12:10.062
So tell, tell! How you two met.

12:10.146 --> 12:11.313
We're dying to hear.

12:11.397 --> 12:13.232
- Yeah, tell us.
- Well, we were at--

12:13.315 --> 12:14.900
- South By.
-Yeah, and...

12:15.359 --> 12:18.529
-Amy was giving me stalker eyes.
-I was interested, but so was he.

12:18.612 --> 12:21.031
-So she reached for the <i>queso.</i>
-Oh, the <i>queso!</i>

12:21.490 --> 12:23.451
-And, um, it felt like...
-It was fate.

12:23.701 --> 12:25.035
Inseparable ever since.

12:25.119 --> 12:26.787
<i> Enjoy it while it lasts.</i>

12:26.871 --> 12:29.290
Yeah, we actually road-tripped
back from Austin.

12:29.373 --> 12:31.250
Got to know each other
a little bit better.

12:31.333 --> 12:33.210
-And what are you doing?

12:33.294 --> 12:35.629
-Amy is an indie film producer.
-<i> Oh, come on.</i>

12:35.713 --> 12:37.798
we're actually already in soft prep

12:37.882 --> 12:39.925
for a film we're trying to get going.

12:40.384 --> 12:41.218
Honey?

12:46.766 --> 12:49.518
He could pretend to care,
like, if he wanted to.

12:50.978 --> 12:53.272
Wow, these waiters are so slow!

12:53.355 --> 12:55.900
Oh, you want a drink?
I'll-- I'll grab you a drink, bunny.

12:55.983 --> 12:57.735
Yeah, could I get a 'buch, please?

12:58.861 --> 13:00.988
-Virgin, obviously.
- Yes.

13:01.113 --> 13:02.281
Appreciate you.

13:05.743 --> 13:07.328
- Here you go.
-Thanks.

13:09.872 --> 13:11.081
What are you doing here?

13:11.165 --> 13:13.751
I told you I'd show up
to give you what you deserve.

13:13.834 --> 13:14.919
So here we are.

13:15.669 --> 13:16.962
Merry Christmas.

13:17.797 --> 13:21.050
<i> How do I get this time bomb</i>
<i>away from you, Love?</i>

13:21.133 --> 13:23.344
-Want to know how I found you?
-I would love to hear.

13:27.097 --> 13:29.600
So, I was feeling like shit
one fine afternoon,

13:29.683 --> 13:32.686
when I saw this clickbait
about how the stars live.

13:32.770 --> 13:34.563
I mean, who doesn't need
a little escapism?

13:34.855 --> 13:36.273
So I clicked and there was this link

13:36.357 --> 13:38.359
about how all the cool kids
go to Henderson's house,

13:38.442 --> 13:40.194
and although
I wasn't familiar with his work,

13:40.277 --> 13:42.655
I was curious about this random douchebag

13:42.738 --> 13:44.824
high as balls on his coffee table,

13:44.907 --> 13:48.536
which is when I first set eyes
on my new dreamy <i>beau.</i>

13:49.078 --> 13:51.997
<i> Of course, your brother</i>
<i>destroyed my life,</i>

13:52.081 --> 13:53.290
<i>our life.</i>

13:53.374 --> 13:55.417
And he's such an idiot.

13:55.626 --> 13:57.670
And I keep watching and...

13:59.630 --> 14:00.631
No.

14:01.799 --> 14:02.800
Couldn't be.

14:04.510 --> 14:05.719
Could not be.

14:05.803 --> 14:07.763
<i> I was trying to help you, Love.</i>

14:07.847 --> 14:09.598
<i>Altruism is dangerous.</i>

14:09.682 --> 14:11.058
Shocked you'd choose LA.

14:11.350 --> 14:12.184
But I found you.

14:12.977 --> 14:13.811
Great.

14:14.228 --> 14:15.437
What's the move?

14:15.521 --> 14:17.857
You gonna tell them this dramatic tale?

14:17.940 --> 14:20.693
I mean, it is their special weekend,

14:20.776 --> 14:23.279
so I'll wait if and when I have to,

14:23.362 --> 14:27.783
But in the meantime, I am going
